Release: stability fixes, multi-gym, Google OAuth, mobile integration

Major work since v2.0.6:

Stability & bug fixes (from audit):
- Fix customer cross-gym data leak (added gym_id filters to all CRUD)
- Fix integrity check SQL bug (gym_id = "" treated as column identifier)
- Fix Realtime zombie channels with exponential backoff cleanup
- Fix DashboardHome unhandled rejection that froze the page
- Fix CustomerProfileCard crash on null first_name/last_name
- Fix migration 14 not re-enabling foreign_keys on failure
- Fix optimistic delete in GymContext (now waits for server success)
- Fix race condition when switching customer profiles rapidly
- Fix PaymentModal silent failure on multi-month payments
- Validate sync_deleted_log table_name against whitelist
- Fix division by zero in capacity percentage
- Sanitize drive_link to prevent javascript: URI XSS

New features:
- "App Movil" tab in customer profile showing:
  - Registration status (registered / invited / not registered)
  - Weight history from mobile app with stats and trend
  - One-click invite button
- Mobile-registered indicator (small icon) in customer list
- Drag & drop for class schedules (move between days/hours)
- Class schedule fully working with bookings sync

Mobile (gym-client-app):
- Google OAuth login via Supabase
- Auth guard centralized at (app) layout
- ErrorBoundary, OfflineIndicator, fetch-with-retry wrapper
- Multi-gym selector when user is linked to multiple gyms
- Gym name shown in selector instead of UUID
- Clear error when authenticated user has no gym access

Cloud:
- New SQL migrations applied to production:
  - google_oauth_autolink: auto-link new users by email
  - multi_gym_support: allow same auth_user across multiple gyms
  - check_client_access returns gyms[] array with gym_name
- inviteToMobile now uses Supabase native templates (consistent emails)

Training service:
- Fix "Expected number, received null" when creating exercises without subcategory
- Accept both videoUrl/video_url variants from form
- Auto-pick first subcategory if user only chose category

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 <noreply@anthropic.com>
